-- p1-parallel-confluence.cell
-- Tests: multiple cells ready simultaneously, confluence property
--
-- Three independent cells share ONE input. They should all be
-- ready at once. Execution order shouldn't matter. A fourth cell
-- depends on all three ‚ÄĒ it's blocked until all complete.

‚äĘ config
  given topic ‚Č° "the moon"
  yield topic

  ‚ä® topic is a noun phrase

‚äĘ poet
  given config‚Üítopic
  yield poem

  ‚ąī Write a haiku about ¬ęconfig‚Üítopic¬Ľ.

  ‚ä® poem is exactly 3 lines
  ‚ä® poem follows 5-7-5 syllable pattern

‚äĘ scientist
  given config‚Üítopic
  yield fact

  ‚ąī State one surprising scientific fact about ¬ęconfig‚Üítopic¬Ľ in a single sentence.

  ‚ä® fact is one sentence
  ‚ä® fact is factually accurate

‚äĘ child
  given config‚Üítopic
  yield question

  ‚ąī Ask a question about ¬ęconfig‚Üítopic¬Ľ the way a curious 5-year-old would.

  ‚ä® question ends with a question mark
  ‚ä® question uses simple vocabulary

‚äĘ= combine
  given poet‚Üípoem
  given scientist‚Üífact
  given child‚Üíquestion
  yield document

  ‚äĘ= document ‚Üź "POEM:\n" + poet‚Üípoem + "\n\nFACT:\n" + scientist‚Üífact + "\n\nQUESTION:\n" + child‚Üíquestion

  ‚ä® document contains all three inputs
